<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="24" type="material examined">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
Eleven females, Russia: Tyumen Province, Tyumen region, vicinity of settlement Narimanovo, 
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="57.365555">57°21'56&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="65.13917">65°08'21&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, in the nest of ants 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius flavus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavus">Lasius flavus</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius), 30 July 2014, coll. V.A. Stolbov.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
This species was described from Ukraine from ants 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tetramorium caespitum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caespitum">Tetramorium caespitum</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation author="Sevastianov, VD" journalOrPublisher="Vestnik Zoologii" pageId="14" pageNumber="27" pagination="25 - 29" title="New species of mites of the family Pygmephoridae (Tarsonemina, Trombidiformes)." volume="6" year="1981">Sevastianov 1981</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Khaustov, AA" journalOrPublisher="Vestnik Zoologii" pageId="13" pageNumber="26" pagination="387 - 393" title="New and little known species of mites of the genus Caesarodispus (Acari, Heterostigmata, Microdispidae) associated with ants (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Ukraine." url="http://www.degruyter.com/view/j/vzoo.2009.43.issue-5/v10058-009-0017-7/v10058-009-0017-7.xml" volume="43" year="2009">Khaustov (2009)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed it based on type material. It was also recorded from Iran from 
<taxonomicName authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnothorax" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Temnothorax</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<bibRefCitation author="Loghmani, A" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="13" pageNumber="26" pagination="273 - 278" title="New species and new record of the genus Caesarodispus (Acari: Heterostigmatina: Microdispidae) phoretic on Temnothorax sp. (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)." url="10.3161/000345414X680627" volume="64" year="2014">Loghmani et al 2014</bibRefCitation>
). This is a new record for the fauna of Russia.
</paragraph>
